- <i>(all)</i> Yeah!

350
00:29:28,268 --> 00:29:30,729
- You really wanna see your monster?
- <i>(all)</i> Yeah!

351
00:29:30,812 --> 00:29:32,898
Here's your monster.

352
00:29:37,569 --> 00:29:40,572
His name... is Izzy Berkowitz!

353
00:29:40,656 --> 00:29:42,741
- Let's get him!
- String him up!

354
00:29:42,824 --> 00:29:45,035
Get your hands off him!

355
00:29:45,702 --> 00:29:49,164
- You let him go.
- I intercepted a package.

356
00:29:49,247 --> 00:29:53,168
How would you like your face
to intercept my fist, coconuthead?

357
00:29:53,251 --> 00:29:55,170
Your kid's a monster!

358
00:29:58,757 --> 00:30:01,426
That is my son you're talkin' about!

359
00:30:03,261 --> 00:30:05,514
What if somebody talked about you
like that?

360
00:30:05,597 --> 00:30:08,141
- Mulder?
- You may have been right, Scully.

361
00:30:08,225 --> 00:30:11,103
What, that they
can be reduced to cultural stereotypes?

362
00:30:11,186 --> 00:30:14,022
- They unmasked the monster.
- Don't start that with me.

363
00:30:14,106 --> 00:30:16,483
I may have found
something saying otherwise.

364
00:30:16,566 --> 00:30:19,778
The residue on the frying pan
was an agricultural product,

365
00:30:19,861 --> 00:30:22,781
used to anaesthetise herds of animals.

366
00:30:22,864 --> 00:30:24,825
- Used by who?
- Farmers,

367
00:30:24,908 --> 00:30:28,328
who must register with the FDA
even to have it in their possession.

368
00:30:28,412 --> 00:30:31,498
- Is there someone registered locally?
