383
00:33:43,190 --> 00:33:44,649
BY Whom?

384
00:33:53,116 --> 00:33:55,660
- It's alive.
- I've seen it.

385
00:33:56,536 --> 00:33:58,622
In the barn, burying the old man.

386
00:33:59,873 --> 00:34:01,958
<i>(angry shouts)</i>

387
00:34:06,796 --> 00:34:08,048
He's a killer!

388
00:34:09,382 --> 00:34:10,634
Murderer!

389
00:34:12,969 --> 00:34:15,222
Where's the monster?

390
00:34:27,234 --> 00:34:31,196
Whatever you have in mind, I'm gonna
have to ask you to stop right there.

391
00:34:31,279 --> 00:34:33,573
We have come for the murderer!

392
00:34:34,491 --> 00:34:38,787
- What makes you think he's here?
- I've seen him with my own eyes.

393
00:34:38,870 --> 00:34:42,666
- He is not a man. He is a monster!
- <i>(all)</i> Yeah!

394
00:34:42,999 --> 00:34:46,586
The fiend must be found,
and then we'll letjustice take its course!

395
00:34:46,670 --> 00:34:48,255
<i>(all)</i> Yeah!

396
00:34:48,338 --> 00:34:51,007
We'll search every crevice, every ravine!

397
00:34:51,091 --> 00:34:55,095
- Get him alive if you can, but you get him!
- <i>(all)</i> Yeah!

398
00:35:29,587 --> 00:35:33,174
There's only one way Polidori
could have seen that monster.

399
00:35:33,258 --> 00:35:36,303
If he was out here himself.

400
00:35:37,762 --> 00:35:39,723
Mulder.

401
00:35:47,981 --> 00:35:51,151
We're federal agents,
and we're armed! Come on out!

402
00:35:59,909 --> 00:36:01,995
Scully, look at this.

403
00:36:06,291 --> 00:36:08,376
<i>(Scully)</i> H <i>uh_</i>

404
00:36:09,419 --> 00:36:11,504
<i>(Creak)</i>

405
00:36:25,643 --> 00:36:29,522
- Oh, my God.
- You're gonna have to come out of there.

406
00:36:31,608 --> 00:36:33,693
We're not gonna hurt you.

407
00:36:35,487 --> 00:36:38,865
- Think he understands?
- I hope not.

408
00:36:40,241 --> 00:36:41,951
He looks frightened.

409
00:36:43,119 --> 00:36:48,124
We're gonna have to get him out of here,
Scully. They're gonna kill him.

410
00:36:48,833 --> 00:36:50,919
The barn's on fire!

411
00:37:29,666 --> 00:37:32,127
There it is!

412
00:37:58,361 --> 00:38:01,072
- Let him go!
- Where is he?

413
00:38:01,156 --> 00:38:03,366
You let him go or we'll burn him out.

414
00:38:03,741 --> 00:38:07,495
Where is he? Show the world
your horrid, lumpy face!

415
00:38:07,579 --> 00:38:09,706
<i>(all)</i> Yeah!

416
00:38:15,003 --> 00:38:17,797
- That's him.
- Uck.

417
00:38:18,423 --> 00:38:22,552
That repulsive physiognomy
is the vilest perversion of science.

418
00:38:23,595 --> 00:38:28,057
- Created by whom?
- A pale student of my most hallowed arts,

419
00:38:28,141 --> 00:38:31,352
whose life was taken
by that which he gave life.

420
00:38:31,936 --> 00:38:36,524
By his own horrible creation, by that
monstrosity that you see before you.

421
00:38:36,608 --> 00:38:39,402
Who's he talkin' about?

422
00:38:40,487 --> 00:38:43,072
- My <i>father.</i>
<i>- (gasps)</i>

423
00:38:44,741 --> 00:38:48,620
- No.
- (Shaineh) He can talk.

424
00:38:48,703 --> 00:38:50,872
Your ears deceive you.

425
00:38:51,122 --> 00:38:53,875
- <i>It's</i> a <i>trick.</i>
- <i>(angry shouts)</i>

426
00:38:59,464 --> 00:39:03,092
I'm sorry, my voice is damaged
by the gaseous chemical.

427
00:39:04,010 --> 00:39:06,262
But I would like to explain myself.

428
00:39:08,473 --> 00:39:12,810
Despite my appearance, which you see
is quite horrible to the human senses,

429
00:39:12,894 --> 00:39:16,898
I... have never acted to harm another soul.

430
00:39:17,315 --> 00:39:20,693
- These are fiendish lies.
- Quiet.

431
00:39:25,823 --> 00:39:28,076
25 years ago,

432
00:39:28,159 --> 00:39:30,954
my father, having only one son -

433
00:39:32,372 --> 00:39:37,877
a spiteful, hateful man of science,
incapable of the deeper sentiments -

434
00:39:39,128 --> 00:39:45,385
he came to realise that this son
had been conducting secret experiments,

435
00:39:45,468 --> 00:39:49,264
of which I was the most
unfortunate product.

436
00:39:49,681 --> 00:39:51,766
<i>(crowd gasps)</i>

437
00:39:53,059 --> 00:39:59,065
A simple man, he rescued me
and loved me in spite of my deformities.

438
00:40:00,358 --> 00:40:04,070
But as time passed,
I grew restless for friends of my own.

439
00:40:05,738 --> 00:40:08,825
Because I couldn't
go to school or play sports,

440
00:40:09,742 --> 00:40:12,245
or even show my face outside this farm,

441
00:40:13,288 --> 00:40:16,708
my father set out to learn his son's science,

442
00:40:16,791 --> 00:40:21,045
so that before he died
he might create for me a mate.

443
00:40:21,921 --> 00:40:24,007
Uh-oh.

444
00:40:25,091 --> 00:40:27,468
Alas, my father was a simple man,

445
00:40:29,137 --> 00:40:34,267
his heart close to the soil
he worked, the animals he tended.

446
00:40:37,645 --> 00:40:40,189
The experiments he attempted,
too advanced.

447
00:40:40,273 --> 00:40:43,776
The science, too complex
for his understanding.

448
00:40:43,860 --> 00:40:47,864
The results of his experiments,
unsatisfactory.

449
00:40:57,206 --> 00:41:00,585
I still... You mean lzzy...?

450
00:41:01,878 --> 00:41:03,963
But who's the father?

451
00:41:08,176 --> 00:41:11,512
Suffice to say, his experiments failed.

452
00:41:12,972 --> 00:41:15,308
My father is dead.

453
00:41:21,189 --> 00:41:24,275
I am alone and miserable.

454
00:41:24,359 --> 00:41:28,946
But one as deformed and horrible as myself
would not deny herself to me.

455
00:41:30,114 --> 00:41:35,495
If this being you can create,
then I will take blame as a murderer.

456
00:41:37,497 --> 00:41:40,166
I don't know how to recreate you.

457
00:41:43,544 --> 00:41:46,005
You were a mistake.

458
00:41:52,053 --> 00:41:54,138
What we did was wrong.

459
00:41:54,847 --> 00:41:58,017
But in our trespasses,
we gave you a loving son.

460
00:41:59,894 --> 00:42:02,980
And in your homes,

461
00:42:03,064 --> 00:42:06,067
I went places I'd never dreamed of.

462
00:42:06,401 --> 00:42:12,198
With your books and your records and your
home media centres, I learned of the world,

463
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:16,911
and of a mother's love that I'll never know.

464
00:42:22,458 --> 00:42:25,086
Cher loved that boy so much.

465
00:42:27,255 --> 00:42:30,800
Hey. He's no monster.

466
00:42:38,266 --> 00:42:40,268
Arrest me, then, as you will.

467
00:42:52,739 --> 00:42:54,824
<i>(Siren)</i>

